COPS in KZN have made a huge drug bust at the Durban Harbour. They seized 380kg of cocaine as they intensified their efforts in disrupting and dismantling organised drug trafficking syndicates. Police spokeswoman Brigadier Athlenda Mathe said they acted on a tip-off about a vessel coming into the country from South America on Thursday, 23 February. ALSO READ: Farmers relieved after escaped lioness found! “The team immediately operationalised the information and conducted surveillance where they identified the vessel. Together with SARS customs officials and K9 dogs, the teams identified the container this morning with 12 bags of cocaine with a street value of R171 million,” said Mathe.  You must be SIGNED IN to read comments “Well done to all teams involved including our Transnational Drug Trafficking investigations unit. This should send a stern warning to all drug traffickers using our harbours that South Africa continues to intensify its efforts to dismantle and disrupt the global drug trafficking trade,” said acting national police commissioner, Lieutenant-General Tebello Mosikili. Mathe added that no arrests have been made and investigations were continuing to establish the source and destination of the drugs. 